{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Armenabad / Բերքաձոր |native_name = Berkadzor |settlement_type = village |pushpin_map = Republic of Artsakh |pushpin_mapsize = 300 |subdivision_type = ''[[de jure]]'' Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|Azerbaijan}} |subdivision_type1 = ''de jure'' [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Khojali Rayon|Khojali]] |subdivision_type2 = ''[[de facto]]'' Country |subdivision_name2 = {{flag|Artsakh}} |subdivision_type3 = ''de facto'' [[Administrative divisions of the Republic of Artsakh|Province]] |subdivision_name3 = [[Askeran Region|Askeran]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = 2005 |population_total = 165 |population_density_km2 = auto |timezone = [[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST = [[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset_DST = +5 |coordinates = {{coord|39|52|34|N|46|46|54|E|region:{{xb|NKR}}|display=inline,title}} |elevation_m = 619 |area_code = |website = }}
'''Armenabad''' ({{lang-hy|Բերքաձոր, '''Berkadzor'''}}) is a village in the [[Khojali Rayon]] of [[Azerbaijan]]. Since the [[Nagorno-Karabakh war]] the town has been administered by the ''de facto'' [[Republic of Artsakh]] as part of [[Askeran Region|Askeran Province]].<ref>http://census.stat-nkr.am/nkr/1-1.pdf</ref>
