[[Category:Lists of accolades by film|Bridge of Spies]]
[[Category:Disney-related lists]]

This is a list of some of the most notable '''bridges and viaducts in [[Stockholm]]''', starting with those located closest to the city centre. Many more bridges and viaducts could, of course, be added, including those on the [[rail transport|rail]] and [[motorway]] networks, and the many [[Grade separation|grade-separated junctions]] in the suburbs which are a product of postwar city planning.<ref name="Dufwa">{{cite book | last = Dufwa | first = Arne | title = Stockholms tekniska historia: Trafik, broar, tunnelbanor, gator | edition = 1st | year = 1985 | publisher = Stockholms gatukontor and Kommittén för Stockholmsforskning | location = Stockholm | isbn = 91-38-08725-1 | pages = 184–219 | chapter = Broar och viadukter för gatutrafiken }}</ref> {| align="center" width="100%" | width="50%" | * [[Norrbro]] * [[Stallbron]] * [[Riksbron]] * [[Vasabron]] * [[Strömsborgsbron]] * [[Riddarholmsbron]] * [[Centralbron]] (two bridges) * [[Hebbes Bro]] * [[Slussen]] (several bridges) * [[Strömbron]] * [[Skeppsholmsbron]] * [[Kastellholmsbron]] * [[Stadshusbron]] * [[Klarabergsviadukten]] * [[Kungsbron]] * [[Blekholmsbron]] * [[Barnhusbron]] * [[Sankt Eriksbron]] * [[Ekelundsbron]] (formerly ''Karlbergsbron'') * [[Morianbron]] * [[Karlbergsbron]] * [[Djurgårdsbron]] * [[Djurgårdsbrunnsbron]] * [[Beckholmsbron]] * [[Lilla Sjötullsbron]] * [[Västerbron]] (two bridges and one viaduct) * [[Mariebergsbron]] (formerly ''Lilla Essingebron'') * [[Långholmsbron]] * [[Pålsundsbron]] * [[Reimersholmsbron]] | width="50%" | * [[Malmskillnadsbron]] (taking [[Malmskillnadsgatan]] over [[Kungsgatan, Stockholm|Kungsgatan]]) * [[Bridge of Regeringsgatan]] (taking [[Regeringsgatan]] over Kungsgatan) * [[Laduviksbron]] * [[Ålkistebron]] * [[Lidingöbron]] (two bridges) * [[Husarbron]] * [[Danviksbron]] (two bridges) * [[Skansbron]] * [[Skanstullsbron]] * [[Johanneshovsbron]] * [[Årstabroarna]] (two bridges) * [[Liljeholmsbron]] (two bridges) * [[Tranebergsbron]] (three bridges) * [[Essingeleden]] (an 8-km motorway, 4&nbsp;km of which consists of bridges and viaducts) * [[Fredhällsbron]] (part of [[Essingeleden]]) * [[Essingebron]] (part of [[Essingeleden]]) * [[Gröndalsbron]] (two bridges: part of [[Essingeleden]] and [[Tvärbanan]]) * [[Solnabron]] * [[Huvudstabron]] * [[Sickla kanalbro]] * [[Sicklauddsbron]] * [[Sickla Allébro]] * [[Alviksbron]] (part of [[Tvärbanan]]) * [[Fredriksdalsbron]] (part of [[Tvärbanan]]) |}
== Historical == * [[Sveabron]] (where present-day [[Odengatan]] passes over [[Sveavägen]]) * [[Nybro (bridge)|Nybro]] or [[Stora Ladugårdslandsbron]] (across today's [[Berzelii Park]]) * [[Näckströms bro]] (connecting [[Norrmalm]] and [[Blasieholmen]])
Additionally, during the cold winters in the 19th century, ice in the city harbour made it necessary to replace ferries by temporary [[pontoon bridge]]s sometimes more than 300 m in length.<ref name="Dufwa" />
