This is a list of countries and dependencies with a permanent population that have no legal political parties. Some have opposition groups that operate clandestinely.

== Monarchies==
*{{flag|Bahrain}} – Political "parties" are banned, but political "societies" are allowed. The media, however, usually refer to these formations as "parties".
*{{flag|Oman}} – Political parties are banned.
*{{flag|Kuwait}} – Political "parties" are not legally recognized, but political blocs are allowed. The media, however, usually refer to these blocs as "parties".
*{{flag|Qatar}} – Political parties are banned.
*{{flag|Saudi Arabia}} – Political parties are banned.<ref>https://www.state.gov/j/drl/rls/hrrpt/humanrightsreport/index.htm?year=2012&dlid=204381
</ref><ref>http://arabia2day.com/tag/umma-islamic-party/</ref>
*{{flag|United Arab Emirates}} – Political parties are banned.
*{{flag|Vatican City|name=Vatican City State}}
*{{flag|Tuvalu}}
*{{flag|Brunei}}

