'''Mount Gimie''' is the tallest mountain on the island of [[Saint Lucia]]. The mountain's peak reaches 950&nbsp;m (3117&nbsp;ft). It is of volcanic origin and is covered by lush tropical rainforest.{{Citation needed|date=January 2009}}
